citations:
    citation-agot-bran-v:
        source: source-agot
        properties:
            locator: "Bran V"
            text_from_source: "He sat straight atop his horse, watching as the iron portcullis was winched upward. Try as he might to keep calm, his heart was fluttering in his chest."
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "Bran's first ride outside Winterfell since his fall, on his specially trained mare Dancer. He rides with Robb, Theon, and guards into the wolfswood. Robb tells Bran that Jory Cassel, Wyl, and Heward were killed by Jaime Lannister, and that Ned's leg is shattered. They are ambushed by Night's Watch deserters and wildlings; Stiv holds Bran hostage. Theon Greyjoy shoots Stiv with a broadhead arrow, killing him. Osha (a wildling woman) surrenders to Robb and is taken prisoner."
